                <p id="footer-graf" class="footer-type">
                    Welcome to <em>Education Matters</em> for April 2014. Spring is here, and that makes us think of things that grow. Things that grow makes us think about our friends at Edison Elementary, just a few blocks south of campus. They're competing for a Seeds of Change grant to expand and improve their service-learning-related Schoolhouse Garden, but they need your vote. Just go to their
                    <a href="http://uocoe.me/1efw79k" target="_blank">
                    voting page
                    </a>
                    and click the button&mdash;no registration required.
                    <br/>
                    <br/>
                    <em>Education Matters</em> is distributed about twice per term, with one summer issue. Click
                    <a href="mailto:edmatters@uoregon.edu" target="_blank">
                    here
                    </a>
                    or the "E-mail <em>Ed Matters</em>" link below to contact the editor; physical letters are always welcome at the mailing address below.
                    <br/>
